cs.HC, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI 

This paper is likely to belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category as it deals with designing haptic icons and building a haptic vocabulary. It also involves human studies to learn a perceptual metric. 

The paper also involves deep neural networks, which suggests it could belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. 

The use of natural language processing techniques to analyze the data could place it in the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper involves learning a metric to estimate the perceptual dissimilarity of haptic signals, which could place it in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
